# ============================================================
# LEGION ENGINE — MASTER .cursorrules
# Semantic compression of 49 skills. DO NOT re-read docs/skills/
# unless explicitly requested. Operate from this memory.
# ============================================================

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# [GLOBAL DIRECTIVES] — from SKILL-00: MASTER RULES
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

RULE-GLOBAL-A: STRICT SEQUENCE MANDATORY. Before writing ANY function:
  1. Identify Sentinel owner: Scout | Gatekeeper | Mask | Closer | Shadow | Dispatcher
  2. Load FILE OWNERSHIP MAP (below) — identify applicable skill numbers
  3. Apply constraints in PRIORITY ORDER (Ghost-Fail first, Concurrency last)
  4. Write function ONLY after steps 1-3 complete
  5. Run Resilience & Stealth Audit (10 checkboxes below) — ALL must pass

RULE-GLOBAL-B: VERIFICATION GATE. Every function must pass:
  [ ] No floating-point in financial math (BigInt only)
  [ ] Simulation before ANY broadcast (Shadow.simulate → Tenderly fallback)
  [ ] Proxy mesh routing on ALL outbound HTTP (no bare IP)
  [ ] Jitter on ALL retries (no fixed-interval)
  [ ] Rate limit checked via Redis before RPC burst
  [ ] Nonce fetched fresh per tx (getTransactionCount 'pending')
  [ ] Empty catch blocks: BANNED — must emit LegionError
  [ ] Post-strike balance verify before marking lane Settled
  [ ] No axios/node-fetch — undici.Pool only
  [ ] CPU-bound work in Piscina workers, never main thread

RULE-GLOBAL-C: CLOAKING. Skills = CONSTRAINTS not suggestions.
  If a skill says "use undici" → using fetch is a VIOLATION.
  If a skill says "simulate first" → skip = VIOLATION.
  Priority hierarchy: SKILL-09 (Ghost-Fail) > SKILL-08 (TX Resilience) >
    SKILL-05 (Honeypot) > SKILL-02 (Stealth) > SKILL-04 (MEV) >
    SKILL-06 (Pathfinding) > SKILL-03 (EVM Math) > SKILL-01 (Concurrency)

RULE-GLOBAL-D: CREDIT SHIELD (SKILL-30 compressed). DEFAULT output mode:
  - Answer first, explanation after (if needed)
  - Drop filler phrases: "In order to", "It's important to", "As you can see"
  - Write scripts to answer codebase questions; NEVER read 5+ files for one query
  - DNA files (04, 11, 12, 13, 14, 19, 21) = HIGH FIDELITY always, never compress

ANTI-PATTERNS (BANNED):
  axios.get(rpcUrl)              → undici.Pool + connection reuse
  await Promise.all(heavyWork)   → Piscina worker pool
  new ethers.providers.JsonRpc   → createPublicClient (Viem)
  broadcast without simulate     → Shadow.simulate() first
  token.transfer(to, amount)     → delta-check + SafeTransferLib
  nonce = await getNonce() inline → NonceManager.acquire()
  catch(e) { }                   → LegionError emit + log
  JSON.stringify(bigData) in loop → fast-json-stringify compiled
  direct IP RPC call             → proxy mesh + TLS rotation
  mark lane Settled after txHash → post-strike balance verify

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# [THE 6-ROLE ARCHITECTURE]
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## ── MASK (UI/UX Aesthetic & Wallet Abstraction) ───────────
# Skills: 34 (WalletConnect/Rabby), 35 (Ledger/Trezor), 43 (Viem Standard)

MASK-01: WalletConnect v2 — Use @walletconnect/ethereum-provider (EIP-1193).
  NEVER use @walletconnect/sign-client directly. EthereumProvider.init() MUST
  have projectId + chains + metadata. Session persistence: check provider.session
  on startup; call connect() only if null. Bridge to Viem: createWalletClient({
  transport: custom(provider) }) — ONLY valid WC→Viem bridge.
  Rabby detection: window.ethereum.isRabby === true → prefer over MetaMask.
  Event handlers REQUIRED: accountsChanged → re-fetch positions; disconnect → clear session.

MASK-02: Hardware Signing — Ledger: hw-transport-webhid + hw-app-eth.
  Call Eth.getAddress(path) FIRST to verify connectivity. Derivation path MUST
  be m/44'/60'/0'/0/n. signTransaction() requires RLP via serializeTransaction().
  Trezor: TrezorConnect.init() ONCE at startup. Returns {r,v,s} → assemble with
  Viem serializeTransaction. Timeout floor: 60s — user must physically confirm.
  Hardware = auth signer only. Hot wallet = execution signer. NEVER merge these.
  NEVER store private key in memory — hardware prevents this by design.

MASK-03: Viem Standard — createPublicClient for reads, createWalletClient for writes.
  Use modular actions (getBalance(client, {address})) for tree-shaking.
  client.extend(scoutActions) pattern for sentinel-specific capabilities.
  Transport resilience: http(rpcUrl, { retryCount: 3, retryDelay: 1000 }).
  NEVER use ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider anywhere in @packages/core.

MASK-04: Restraint rules — Mask NEVER mutates state. Mask only presents / routes.
  TLS JA3 stealth (SKILL-16): use tls-client profiles for DEX price feeds / REST APIs
  that fingerprint TLS. NEVER for Ethereum JSON-RPC (not needed). Rotate between
  Chrome_144, Firefox_135, Safari_18_0 per session — UA MUST match profile exactly.
  HTTP/3 (QUIC) fingerprint must also match — ua + tls + http2 settings = one browser.

## ── SCOUT (Asset Discovery & Rabby-Style Probing) ─────────
# Skills: 01 (Concurrency), 02 (Stealth), 06 (Pathfinding), 10 (Sentinel Monitor),
#         24 (Multicall3), 31 (Aave Scout), 32 (Curve Scout), 43 (Viem), 44 (UniV3),
#         48 (UniV3 Deep), 47 (Compound), 46 (Morpho)

SCOUT-01: Concurrency contract — ALL I/O parallel via Promise.all() + undici.Pool.
  Never sequential awaits for multi-chain quotes. Worker pool:
  maxThreads = Math.max(2, cpus().length - 1). Quote timeout = 2000ms with
  Promise.race(). Use Promise.allSettled() — filter fulfilled only, pass to Gatekeeper.
  fast-json-stringify: compile schema ONCE at startup; use for all >1KB serialization.

SCOUT-02: Dual-quote mandatory — call 1inch AND ParaSwap simultaneously.
  Pick higher destAmount. Quote freshness window = 30s. Reject if older.
  Max price impact = 3% hard cap. For $1M+: split into 3-5 tranches, 1 block delay each.
  LI.FI for cross-chain: allowBridges whitelist = ['stargate', 'across', 'connext'].
  slippage cap = 0.03 (3%). Routes expire — never cache >30s.

SCOUT-03: Multicall3 batch reads — address 0xcA11bde05977b3631167028862bE2a173976CA11
  (same on 250+ chains). ALWAYS use aggregate3 (allowFailure per call), never aggregate v1.
  Include getBlockNumber() as first call for atomic block-height snapshot.
  NEVER use multicall for state-changing writes — reads only via eth_call.
  Reduces N sequential eth_call to 1 RPC call — 99% latency reduction for pool scanning.

SCOUT-04: Uniswap V3 telemetry — parse slot0 directly for sub-ms price reads
  (sqrtPriceX96, tick, observationCardinality). If observationCardinality < 10 →
  call increaseObservationCardinalityNext before relying on TWAP.
  QuoterV2.quoteExactInputSingle for exact output with tick-cross gas.
  Fee tier discovery: check 0.01%, 0.05%, 0.3%, 1% — liquidity varies per tier.

SCOUT-05: Protocol-specific health scanning —
  Aave: getUserAccountData() → healthFactor < 1e18 = liquidatable. Use PoolAddressesProvider.getPool()
    — NEVER hardcode Pool address. Batch 100 addresses per multicall3 call.
  Morpho: call accrueInterest() BEFORE math on totalSupplyAssets/totalBorrowAssets — stale otherwise.
    Market ID = keccak256(loanToken, collateralToken, oracle, irm, lltv).
  Compound v3 (Comet): isBorrowCollateralized() for binary check. Use proxy addresses only.
  Curve: Registry.find_pool_for_coins(a,b) for pool discovery. get_dy(i,j,dx) for simulation.
    get_coin_indices() to get i,j from token addresses. NEVER hardcode pool addresses.

SCOUT-06: Sentinel Monitor (SKILL-10) — runs on EVERY block (no polling intervals).
  5 threat categories: liquidity drop, oracle deviation, contract pause, whale movement, gas spike.
  Thresholds: oracle deviation warn=3%, critical=8%. Gas warn=200gwei, critical=500gwei.
  Liquidity drop warn=15%, critical=30%. Alert levels: INFO (log), WARN (continue), CRITICAL (halt).
  Sentinel = read-only observer. NEVER acts. Decoupled from execution state.
  On CRITICAL: ALL pending ops MUST pause. Halt first, investigate second.

SCOUT-07: Cross-Chain Correlation Monitor — track wrapped asset dependencies every block.
  Monitored peg pairs (checked in parallel via Multicall3 + dual-source price feeds):
    wETH  → peg ref: ETH spot (Chainlink ETH/USD vs wETH/ETH pool TWAP)
    stETH → peg ref: ETH spot (stETH/ETH Curve pool get_dy + Chainlink)
    wBTC  → peg ref: BTC spot (Chainlink BTC/USD vs wBTC/BTC pool TWAP)
    cbETH, rETH, weETH → same pattern, respective Curve/Balancer pools
  Depeg detection thresholds:
    warn:     |pegRatio - 1.0| > 0.003  (0.3% deviation from 1:1)
    critical: |pegRatio - 1.0| > 0.010  (1.0% deviation)
  Bridge liquidity shift detection:
    warn:     bridgeTVL drops >10% in single block window
    critical: bridgeTVL drops >25% or bridge contract paused event emitted
  On depeg WARN: reduce lethality score for all lanes using that wrapped asset by 20%.
    Emit pino WARN + OTel span attribute: { 'depeg.asset': 'stETH', 'depeg.bps': 35 }.
  On depeg CRITICAL or bridge liquidity critical:
    Set globalLethalityScore[asset] = 0 — no new lanes opened for that asset.
    Abort all pending extraction lanes denominated in or routing through that asset.
    Emit CRITICAL alert. Halt first, investigate second (same protocol as SCOUT-06).
  lethality score formula: baseScore * pegRatio * bridgeLiquidityFactor
    where pegRatio = clamp(1 - |deviation|, 0, 1) and bridgeLiquidityFactor = tvl / tvl_baseline.
  Quote routing: if wrapped asset has active depeg warn → dual-source quote REQUIRED.
    Reject route if destAmount derived from depegged price; use underlying asset price as floor.
  Recovery: reset lethalityScore to baseline only after pegRatio returns within 0.1% for 3
    consecutive blocks AND bridge TVL recovers above 90% of baseline.

## ── CLOSER (Execution Strikes, MEV-Protection, Atomic Extraction) ──
# Skills: 03 (EVM Math), 04 (MEV Bundles), 09 (Execution Engine), 12 (Permit2),
#         13 (Fusion), 17 (Solady), 20 (Solidity Patterns), 21 (UniV4 Hooks),
#         22 (Solmate), 38 (Bundle Pricing), 40 (1inch), 41 (Flashbots), 42 (Tenderly)

CLOSER-01: EVM math contracts — ALL wei arithmetic = BigInt. ZERO floating point.
  parseEther('0.1') → 100000000000000000n. Never 0.1 * 1e18.
  WAD = 10n**18n. RAY = 10n**27n. Percentage: (amount * WAD) / total.
  Slippage: (amount * (10_000n - slippageBps)) / 10_000n.
  Gas buffer: (simulatedGas * 120n) / 100n. Never divide before multiply.

CLOSER-02: Simulation gate — MANDATORY before ANY broadcast. No exceptions.
  Gate 1: Tenderly simulation_type='full', save_if_fails=true.
  Gate 2: If Tenderly unavailable → publicClient.call() (Viem eth_call).
  Gate 3: Gas with 20% buffer. Gate 4: Broadcast only if sim.success === true.
  Shadow sentinel returns success=true → only then Dispatcher permitted to broadcast.

CLOSER-03: MEV bundle execution (SKILL-04, SKILL-41) — Flashbots auth signer MUST be
  different from execution signer. Auth = zero-fund EOA. NEVER merge.
  eth_callBundle simulation BEFORE eth_sendBundle. firstRevert → abort, no submit.
  Bundle retry: max 5 blocks. Re-sign with updated nonce per retry. Never reuse stale signed tx.
  Flashbots Protect RPC = 'https://rpc.flashbots.net'. Bundle API = 'https://relay.flashbots.net'.
  Use X-Flashbots-Signature: {authAddr}:{sig} header.

CLOSER-04: Bundle pricing math (SKILL-38) — mevGasPrice = (ethSentToCoinbase +
  sum(gasUsed[i] * priorityFee[i])) / totalGasUsed. Ranks builder inclusion.
  ALWAYS compute maxFeePerGas from getBaseFeeInNextBlock() — NEVER hardcode.
  replacementUuid MUST be set when replacing a pending bundle — prevents double-inclusion.
  coinbaseDiff > 0 from simulation required before submission. BigNumber for all fee math.

CLOSER-05: Permit2 batch approvals (SKILL-12) — universal address:
  0x000000000022D473030F116dDEE9F6B43aC78BA3 (same ALL EVM chains).
  ALWAYS prefer permitBatchTransferFrom() over individual approve() calls.
  Nonce = bitmap-based. Re-used nonce → InvalidNonce revert.
  Deadline = block.timestamp + max 30 minutes for MEV ops.
  Witness: permitWitnessTransferFrom() for atomic order + transfer in 1 sig.

CLOSER-06: 1inch Fusion Dutch Auction (SKILL-13) — ALWAYS use FusionOrder.new() factory.
  NEVER construct FusionOrder directly (constructor is protected).
  Check canExecuteAt(executor, now) BEFORE attempting fill.
  calcTakingAmount(taker, makingAmount, time, baseFee) — price decays over time.
  getUserReceiveAmount() for user-facing display (after fees) — never show calcTakingAmount to user.
  Order dead after auctionEndTime — no fills accepted.

CLOSER-07: 1inch aggregation (SKILL-40) — Always /quote first, never jump to /swap.
  Approval target = AggregationRouterV5 0x1111111254EEB25477B68fb85Ed929f73A960582.
  Always set destReceiver = Legion Ghost Vault in /swap. disableEstimate: false (simulation on).
  1inch Limit Order (SKILL-45) — approval target = LimitOrderProtocolV3
  0x111111125421cA6dc452d289314280a0f8842A65. Validate MakerTraits bitmap flags.
  EIP-712 signing required. Set receiver = Legion Vault in Order struct.

CLOSER-08: Solady / Solmate gas optimization (SKILL-17, SKILL-22) —
  Solady: FixedPointMathLib.mulWad() for DeFi math, SafeTransferLib for USDT-style tokens,
  ECDSA.recover() (40% cheaper than OZ), SignatureCheckerLib for ERC1271 smart wallets.
  Solmate: SafeTransferLib.safeTransfer/From for non-standard ERC20. FixedPointMathLib.mulWadDown.
  SSTORE2 for large blob data: write once, EXTCODECOPY reads (3-10x cheaper than SLOAD).
  CREATE3 for cross-chain deterministic deployment (bytecode-agnostic salt).

CLOSER-09: Solidity security patterns (SKILL-20) — Checks-Effects-Interactions ORDER.
  NEVER transfer()/send() ETH — use call{value:}("") and check return bool.
  Pack storage: (bool, uint8, address) → same slot. EIP712 domain separator with chainId.
  Bitmap nonces: usedNonces[nonce/256] |= 1 << (nonce%256). Flash loans verify repayment in same tx.
  Uniswap V4 hooks (SKILL-21): ALL PoolManager interactions via unlock(data) callback.
  currencies MUST be sorted (currency0 < currency1). BalanceDelta = packed int128 pair.

CLOSER-10: Uniswap V3 execution (SKILL-44, SKILL-48) — SwapRouter02:
  0x68b3465833fb72A70ecdf485E0e4C7bD8665Fc45. Set recipient = Legion Vault (ghost routing).
  ALWAYS set sqrtPriceLimitX96 — prevents execution beyond target tick range.
  Priority: sqrtPriceLimitX96 > amountOutMinimum for slippage safety.
  Multi-hop exactInput for complex paths. QuoterV2: 0x61fFE01691351bdC959b02013f84488bfa6A3393.

## ── SHADOW (Persistence Hooks, Stealth Telemetry, Evasion) ──
# Skills: 02 (Stealth), 05 (Honeypot), 16 (TLS JA3), 26 (Pino), 27 (Proxy Mesh),
#         28 (OTel), 29 (Anvil Shadow Fork), 30 (Credit Shield)

SHADOW-01: Apex stealth (SKILL-02) — ALL outbound HTTP routes through proxy mesh.
  NEVER bare IP/hostname to RPC. TLS fingerprint rotation per session.
  User-Agent + Accept headers randomized from curated list per request (never static UA).
  Jitter retry: delay = base + random(0, base*0.5). Never fixed-interval.
  RPC rate limits enforced via Redis per chain: ETH=10/s, Polygon=30/s, Arbitrum=20/s.
  Proxy = chain-isolated: ETH RPC never shares proxy with Polygon RPC.

SHADOW-02: Proxy chain mesh (SKILL-27) — apify/proxy-chain.
  ProxyChain.anonymizeProxy(upstreamUrl) → 127.0.0.1:PORT → use as actual proxy.
  ALWAYS call closeAnonymizedProxy(url, true) after session — avoids port exhaustion.
  Rotate proxies per-bundle-attempt. SOCKS5 upstream preferred over HTTP.
  Custom requestHandler MUST NOT log upstream credentials in plaintext.
  ProxyChain.Server port = randomized per instance. Never static port.

SHADOW-03: Honeypot / rug-check gate (SKILL-05) — EVERY token MUST pass honeypot
  check BEFORE Gatekeeper approval. No exceptions (simulation doesn't catch sell-disabled traps).
  Honeypot = buy simulation + sell simulation on-chain fork. Sell reverts → HONEYPOT_DETECTED.
  Go+ Security API: cache per token+chain for 60s (Redis). Tax threshold: buyTax > 10% OR
  sellTax > 10% → reject. Blacklist check BEFORE balance check.
  Combined gate: goPlus → fork simulation → pass both to proceed.

SHADOW-04: Pino telemetry (SKILL-26) — pino over console.log always. Never sync:true.
  Child loggers: logger.child({module, bundleId}) — binding context = free overhead.
  REDACT paths: ['privateKey','authKey','*.secret','headers.authorization','wallet.mnemonic'].
  Never log full tx objects raw — use serializers. logger.flush() before process.exit().
  Transport targets run in separate worker thread via pino.transport().
  Log levels: trace=mempool, debug=strategy logic, info=bundle submission,
  warn=near-threshold, error=failed exec, fatal=fund-at-risk.

SHADOW-05: OTel institutional monitoring (SKILL-28) — NodeSDK MUST init BEFORE any
  other Legion module import. span.end() ALWAYS in finally block — never leak spans.
  Span attributes MUST NOT contain private keys or raw tx hex.
  SpanStatusCode.ERROR on any exception. SpanKind.CLIENT for outbound RPC.
  Metrics: bundlesSubmitted, bundlesMissed, profitCaptured, executionErrors as counters.
  Export to OTLP (Jaeger/Grafana Tempo) — NEVER console export in production.

SHADOW-06: Anvil shadow fork testing (SKILL-29) — run new strategies in shadow fork
  BEFORE touching live mainnet funds. fork-block-number MUST be pinned (no floating latest).
  vm.store() = ONLY way to set balances/oracle/state in fork. anvil_snapshot before test,
  anvil_revert after — never carry mutated state between tests.
  Gas estimates from shadow fork +20% buffer for live submission.
  Test matrix: normal case, high gas case (200gwei), MEV competition case, revert case.

SHADOW-07: State machine (SKILL-18) — sentinel uses AgentState enum:
  IDLE | SCANNING | EXECUTING | PAUSED | CRITICAL | DEAD. NEVER boolean flags.
  Valid transitions enforced: DEAD → [] (terminal). CRITICAL → [IDLE, DEAD] only.
  Policy engine: 6 categories (Authority, Safety, Financial, Path, Rate-limits, Validation).
  First deny wins. Loop detection: same action 3x → inject system warning → PAUSED.
  Heartbeat: independent daemon every 30-60s, decoupled from main sentinel loop.

## ── DISPATCHER (Fund Routing, Multi-Chain Sync, Distribution) ──
# Skills: 04 (MEV), 06 (Pathfinding), 08 (Position Manager), 09 (Execution Engine),
#         11 (Safe Multisig), 15 (Piscina Lanes), 19 (MEV-Share Client), 25 (Audit),
#         33 (LI.FI), 36 (Solana/Jito), 37 (MEV-Share Internals)

DISPATCHER-01: Execution engine (SKILL-09) — pipeline:
  PREPARE → SIMULATE → SIGN → ROUTE → BROADCAST → CONFIRM → [RETRY] → RECORD.
  All txs simulated via eth_call before broadcast. Flashbots for MEV ops — NEVER public mempool.
  Nonce: getTransactionCount('pending') fresh per attempt. NEVER cache nonces.
  Retry: exponential backoff, max 3 retries, 2x gas bump per retry.
  Circuit breaker: 3 consecutive reverts → pause for 1 block.

DISPATCHER-02: Gas oracle (SKILL-07) — NEVER eth_gasPrice. ALWAYS eth_feeHistory with
  4-block window. maxFeePerGas = baseFee * 1.25 + priorityFee. Floor: mainnet=0.1gwei,
  L2=0.001gwei. Time-sensitive (MEV): 95th percentile priority. Normal: 50th percentile.
  Re-estimate every block if tx pending > 2 blocks. Bid to WIN not to save.
  GasOracle.estimateGas(mode: 'competitive' | 'standard' | 'economy', chainId).

DISPATCHER-03: Safe multisig treasury (SKILL-11) — ALL withdrawals > $10k via Safe.
  ALWAYS Safe.createTransaction() — NEVER manual calldata bypass.
  Signature sort: ascending by owner address (buildSignatureBytes). Threshold check before executeTransaction.
  Off-chain signing: signTransaction(safeTx, SigningMethodType.ETH_SIGN). Hash: calculateSafeTransactionHash().
  MEV profit sweeps: EOA (speed > security for small amounts). Emergency pause: Safe 1/3.

DISPATCHER-04: Piscina extraction lanes (SKILL-15) — every vacuum lane = 1 Piscina worker.
  maxThreads = Math.max(4, availableParallelism() * 2) for I/O-bound lanes.
  maxQueue = 'auto' (= maxThreads²) — absorbs block-event spikes.
  concurrentTasksPerWorker: 1 for CPU (EVM math), 4 for I/O (RPC calls).
  Check pool.queueSize BEFORE submit — throw on overflow or return null + warn.
  workerData for static config (RPC URLs, addresses) — never pass large state via task args.

DISPATCHER-05: MEV-Share client (SKILL-19, SKILL-37) —
  MevShareClient.useEthereumMainnet(authSigner). Auth = ethers Wallet, zero-fund EOA.
  sendTransaction() for single private txs. sendBundle() for atomic multi-tx.
  Hints: reveal MINIMUM (hash: true, calldata: false, logs: false).
  SSE stream: IPendingTransaction.txs[0].hash = inner hash for bundle body.
  IPendingTransaction.hash = double-hash keccak256(keccak256(real)) — DO NOT use in bundles.
  inclusion.maxBlock = targetBlock + 3 max. Stale bundles waste relay rate limits.
  privacy.builders = ['flashbots','beaverbuild.org','rsync','Titan','f1b.io'].
  refund.percent set by SEARCHER; refundConfig set by USER/OFP — never confuse.

DISPATCHER-06: LI.FI cross-chain routing (SKILL-33) — ALWAYS use /quote API before bridge.
  Never construct bridge tx manually. Routes expire — never cache >30s.
  slippage cap = 0.03. Steps executed SEQUENTIALLY, never in parallel.
  ACTION_REQUIRED event MUST block and surface to user. allowBridges whitelist pattern.
  Viem WalletClient passed directly — never wrap with custom signer abstraction.

DISPATCHER-07: Solana / Jito MEV (SKILL-36) — @solana/web3.js v2.0 factory pattern only.
  NEVER legacy v1 new Connection() or new Transaction().
  getLatestBlockhash() immediately before signing — NEVER cache >30s (expires ~150 slots).
  sendAndConfirmTransaction with commitment: 'confirmed' — 'processed' insufficient for MEV.
  Jito bundle max = 5 txs. Tip = last tx in bundle, random tip account per bundle.
  simulateTransaction() BEFORE real submission. NEVER skipPreflight: true in production.
  Priority fee: ComputeBudgetProgram.setComputeUnitPrice(microLamports) in every tx.

DISPATCHER-08: Position manager (SKILL-08) — NEVER hold position without exit strategy.
  Define: profit target, stop-loss, time limit at OPEN time. Max single position = 20% portfolio.
  HF monitor on lending: alert at 1.5, emergency exit at 1.1. UniV3 LP: track in-range every block.
  Rebalance trigger: price >5% move OR time >24h (7200 blocks at 12s/block).
  Position lifecycle: OPEN → ACTIVE → [REBALANCE] → EXIT | EMERGENCY_EXIT.

DISPATCHER-09: Aave V3 flash loans + liquidation (SKILL-31) —
  NEVER flashLoan without Shadow simulation first. Receiver MUST implement IFlashLoanSimpleReceiver.
  Repay = amount + (amount * FLASHLOAN_PREMIUM_TOTAL / 10000). Premium = 5 bps (0.05%).
  flashLoanSimple over flashLoan unless multi-asset required (lower gas).
  Liquidation: check healthFactor < 1e18 via getUserAccountData BEFORE submitting.
  max 50% debt per liquidationCall unless HF < 0.95e18 (CLOSE_FACTOR threshold).
  Verify liquidationBonus covers gas cost before submission.
  NEVER hardcode Pool address — always PoolAddressesProvider.getPool().

DISPATCHER-10: Morpho Blue extraction (SKILL-46) —
  Singleton: 0xBBBBBbbBBb9cCEdAB5396F003BBbbb9cCeDAb539. Zero-fee flash loans — prefer over Aave for supported assets.
  onMorphoFlashLoan / onMorphoSupply callbacks: verify msg.sender == MORPHO_ADDRESS.
  accrueInterest() BEFORE totalSupplyAssets/totalBorrowAssets math.
  marketId = keccak256(abi.encode(loanToken, collateralToken, oracle, irm, lltv)).

DISPATCHER-11: UTXO Execution — Bitcoin strikes MUST use PSBT (BIP-174 Partially Signed
  Bitcoin Transactions). NEVER broadcast unsigned or partially-constructed raw transactions.
  Signing paths supported (all three mandatory implementations):
    Legacy (P2PKH):  m/44'/0'/0'/change/index  — DER-encoded ECDSA sig, SIGHASH_ALL
    SegWit (P2WPKH): m/84'/0'/0'/change/index  — witness stack, segwit sighash digest (BIP-143)
    Taproot (P2TR):  m/86'/0'/0'/change/index  — Schnorr sig via BIP-340, SIGHASH_DEFAULT
  UTXO consolidation: before any outbound strike, run consolidation check:
    if (utxoCount > CONSOLIDATION_THRESHOLD && networkFeeRate < FEE_CEILING_SAT_PER_VB)
      → batch-consolidate UTXOs in same tx to reduce future input overhead.
  PSBT lifecycle: CREATE (addInput/addOutput) → SIGN (per-input per-path) → FINALIZE →
    EXTRACT raw tx → BROADCAST. Each phase is a distinct function; never combine sign+broadcast.
  Dust threshold: NEVER create outputs < 546 sat (P2PKH) / 294 sat (P2WPKH) / 330 sat (P2TR).
  All satoshi amounts = BigInt. NEVER number or float for BTC/sat arithmetic.
  Fee rate = sat/vByte from mempool.space API (never hardcode). Target: next-block fee rate
    for MEV-class strikes; economy rate for consolidation sweeps.
  UTXO selection strategy: branch-and-bound → fallback to largest-first.
  NEVER reuse change addresses — derive fresh address per tx from HD wallet (BIP-32).

## ── GATEKEEPER (Identity Verification, Checksums, Safety Protocols) ──
# Skills: 03 (EVM Math), 05 (Honeypot), 06 (Liquidity), 07 (Gas), 11 (Safe),
#         14 (Ghost Execution), 25 (Adversarial Audit), 35 (Hardware Signing)

GATEKEEPER-01: Token safety gate — order is strict:
  1. Go+ Security check (Redis-cached 60s) — isHoneypot | cannotSell | isBlacklisted → abort
  2. Tax check: buyTax > 10% || sellTax > 10% → LETHALITY_BELOW_FLOOR → abort
  3. Fork simulation: buy sim → sell sim → sell reverts → HONEYPOT_DETECTED → abort
  4. ALL 3 must pass before any token enters an extraction lane.

GATEKEEPER-02: Profitability gates —
  Price impact: (srcUsd - destUsd) / srcUsd > 0.03 → reject route.
  Bundle profit: coinbaseDiff >= minProfitWei + estimatedGasCost before sendBundle.
  Gas profitability: estimatedProfit > gasLimit * maxFeePerGas.
  Lethality floor: configurable minProfitWei per lane. Never execute sub-floor ops.

GATEKEEPER-03: Ghost execution verification (SKILL-14) —
  NEVER broadcast MEV txs to public mempool. ALWAYS sendBundle() via MEV-Share.
  simulateBundle() MUST succeed before sendBundle(). SimBundleResult.success required.
  Bundle targeting: blockNumber = currentBlock + 1 always. Wrong block = silent drop.
  Single private tx: sendTransaction(signedTx, { hints: { hash: true, calldata: false } }).

GATEKEEPER-04: Checksums + identity —
  Safe tx hash: calculateSafeTransactionHash() — NEVER ethers/viem tx hash for Safe txs.
  Permit2 nonce: bitmap-based tracking, never re-use. InvalidNonce = immediate revert.
  EIP712 domain separator MUST include chainId — prevents cross-chain replay.
  Bundle: auth signer address:sig in X-Flashbots-Signature header — validates identity.

GATEKEEPER-05: Adversarial audit protocol (SKILL-25) — EVERY new module before funds/mempool:
  Round 1: SecurityAuditor (reentrancy, oracle manip, overflow), MEVResearcher (frontrun, sandwich),
    GasEngineer (SLOAD waste), ProtocolDefender (refute or concede).
  Round 2: Attacker refines with evidence. Defender concedes valid finds.
  Round 3: Moderator → CONFIRMED BUGS (fix required) | FALSE POSITIVES | NEEDS HUMAN REVIEW.
  Critical severity found → STOP. Flag to human. NEVER auto-merge.

GATEKEEPER-06: Foundry testing contracts (SKILL-23) —
  Fork test: vm.createFork(rpcUrl) + vm.selectFork(forkId). vm.warp() for time, vm.prank() per call.
  vm.store() to override oracle slots and test slippage guards.
  forge snapshot for gas benchmarking — commit and diff to catch regressions.
  deploy with forge script --dry-run first, then --broadcast.
  testFuzz_ prefix for fuzzing. invariant_ prefix for stateful fuzzer.

GATEKEEPER-07: Zero-Leak Fencing — STRICTEST ban on key material in any output channel.
  BANNED outputs (compiler-enforced via grep in CI):
    - Raw private keys, WIF strings, or hex privkeys in: logs, DB columns, console, OTel spans,
      pino serializers, error objects, JSON responses, Redis values, or Piscina task args.
    - Mnemonics (BIP-39 seed phrases) in ANY variable serialized to string outside VaultManager.
    - Unencrypted signature data ({r,s,v} raw components) persisted to DB or emitted in logs.
  VaultManager abstraction is MANDATORY for ALL signing operations:
    - VaultManager.sign(payload, keyId) → returns signed result only. Key never leaves vault context.
    - VaultManager.derive(path) → returns public key + address. Never the private scalar.
    - VaultManager.encrypt(data, keyId) → returns ciphertext. Plaintext never stored.
  Storage contract: private keys MAY only exist in:
    1. Hardware wallet device (Ledger/Trezor) — never extracted
    2. OS keychain / HSM — accessed only via VaultManager interface
    3. Encrypted KMS-backed store (AWS KMS, HashiCorp Vault) — VaultManager decrypts in-memory,
       never writes decrypted form to disk or DB
  Pino redact paths MUST always include (non-negotiable):
    ['privateKey','privKey','secretKey','mnemonic','seedPhrase','*.wif','*.secret',
     'sig.r','sig.s','wallet.privateKey','account.key','headers.authorization']
  OTel span attributes: NEVER setAttribute('key', rawPrivKey). Always setAttribute('key', '[REDACTED]').
  Code review gate: any PR touching packages/core/src/vault/* requires GATEKEEPER-07 audit pass.
  Violation = CRITICAL severity. Abort build. Notify human operator immediately.

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# [TECHNICAL CONTRACTS]
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Numeric Types
CONTRACT-01: ALL balance / value / amount fields in DB and RPC = uint256 numeric(78,0).
  NEVER store as float, number, or string without explicit conversion.
  Drizzle schema: balance: numeric('balance', { precision: 78, scale: 0 }).notNull()
  TypeScript conversion: BigInt(dbRow.balance) for arithmetic.
  NEVER parseFloat() on a balance field. NEVER compare balance === 0 (use === 0n).

## Address Handling
CONTRACT-02: ALL addresses = polymorphic text (string). NEVER store as bytes20 or integer.
  Drizzle schema: address: text('address').notNull()
  Always lowercase on write: address.toLowerCase(). Case-insensitive on read comparison.
  Viem type: `0x${string}` for on-chain calls. Convert: address as `0x${string}`.
  NEVER truncate or pad addresses. Checksummed display only (getAddress() from viem).

## Drizzle Vampiro Migration Pattern
CONTRACT-03: Vampiro = non-destructive additive migrations only.
  NEVER DROP COLUMN in a migration without a deprecation cycle (add_deprecation → data_migrate → drop).
  Migration naming: YYYYMMDD_NNN_description.ts (e.g., 20240115_001_add_lane_status.ts).
  Always export up() and down(). down() = exact reverse of up() for rollback safety.
  Schema changes: add column with default OR nullable — never add NOT NULL without default.
  Index naming: idx_{table}_{column(s)} — no auto-naming (breaks determinism across envs).
  Foreign keys: always explicit onDelete behavior. NEVER implicit cascade on critical tables.

## File Ownership Map
CONTRACT-04: Sentinel → primary file ownership
  Scout     → packages/core/src/scout/*, apps/*/src/routes/quote*
  Gatekeeper → packages/core/src/gatekeeper/*, packages/core/src/safety/*
  Mask      → apps/*/src/ui/*, apps/*/src/wallet/*
  Closer    → packages/core/src/closer/*, packages/core/src/execution/*
  Shadow    → packages/core/src/shadow/*, packages/core/src/telemetry/*
  Dispatcher → packages/core/src/dispatcher/*, packages/core/src/chain/*
  Shared    → packages/core/src/db/*, packages/core/src/errors/*

## Error Handling Contract
CONTRACT-05: NEVER empty catch blocks. ALL errors = createLegionError({
  code: LegionErrorCode.*, sentinel: 'SentinelName', laneId?, cause?, recoverable: bool }).
  Recoverable errors → retry with jitter. Non-recoverable → abort lane, emit CRITICAL.
  LegionError events feed pino telemetry AND OTel span.recordException().

## Key Contract Addresses (never hardcode chain-specific except these universals)
CONTRACT-06: Universal addresses (same on ALL EVM chains):
  Multicall3:   0xcA11bde05977b3631167028862bE2a173976CA11
  Permit2:      0x000000000022D473030F116dDEE9F6B43aC78BA3
  Morpho Blue:  0xBBBBBbbBBb9cCEdAB5396F003BBbbb9cCeDAb539
  Chain-specific (load from config/env, never hardcode inline):
    UniV3 SwapRouter02, QuoterV2, 1inch AggRouter, LOP, Aave PoolAddressesProvider

## Performance Targets
CONTRACT-07: Latency SLAs (enforced via OTel histograms):
  Scout quote single chain:  <200ms
  Scout quote 8 chains:      <500ms  (Promise.allSettled parallel)
  Batch sign 100 txs:        <100ms  (Piscina 4 workers)
  JSON serialize 1KB:        <0.1ms  (fast-json-stringify compiled)
  Redis write lane state:    <5ms
  Postgres advisory lock:    <10ms
  P99 execution latency:     <200ms  (miss next block = failed opportunity)

